10. SRS Introduction Section - Document purpose, scope, definitions/acronyms
1. Purpose
This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document defines the functional and non-functional requirements for the Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System (CIRRS). It is intended to be used by the development team, testers, project managers, and stakeholders to understand the system's capabilities and constraints.
2. Scope
The CIRRS is a web-based system designed to manage cybersecurity incidents within an organization. It supports incident reporting, triage, assignment, response, and reporting. The system is limited to incident management and does not include proactive security measures.
3. Definitions and Acronyms

 Term Acronym	Description
       CIRRS	Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System
      UI	User Interface
Incident	A security event that compromises the confidentiality, integrity, or availability of information
Triage	The process of assessing and prioritizing incidents
SOC	Security Operations Center
SLA	Service Level Agreement
